    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted at the program level because the ASTM F1717 protocol is a standardized regulatory benchmark with no alternative load configuration specified for this device class. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, relative difference < 10%) across all 11 constructs at both laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
